ce:section.ce:para:
One focus of this work is the consideration of the non-spherical shape of the graphite particles. For this purpose, the particle model “Sphero-Polygon” of the DEM code Rocky was used in the simulations. The particle shape in Rocky is defined by means of two aspect ratios and its number of corners. Five different particle templates were created per particle set (Fig. 1
                        ). Shape parameters for the particle sets “use case” and “flat” are listed in Table 3
                         and in the Appendix, respectively. Each particle template has four corners to reduce the computational effort.
